<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
    <p>We often need to apply margins or padding to individual elements. In an effort to standardize spacing between elements (whitespace) we use a whitespace declaration which has a corresponding rem value.</p>
    <p>To add space to any element we add a class of <code>u-{type}{direction}-{amount}</code>. For example, if we wanted to add 16px of margin below an element, we would add a class of <code>.u-mb-3</code>.
  </div>
</div>

